        "summary": "## Summary of Changes\n\n### Backend\n- **Domain.cs** \u2014 Added `UserId` to `Booking` and `CreateBookingRequest` (optional, preserving existing behavior); added auth DTOs: `RegisterRequest`, `LoginRequest`, `UserInfo`; added `BookingError.Unauthenticated`\n- **RestaurantBooking.Api.csproj** \u2014 Added `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Identity.EntityFrameworkCore`, `Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.InMemory`\n- **Data/AppDbContext.cs** (new) \u2014 EF Core DbContext with `AppUser` (extends `IdentityUser` with `Name`), using InMemory database\n- **Program.cs** \u2014 Added ASP.NET Core Identity with cookie auth, antiforgery (CSRF) for state-changing endpoints, CORS with `AllowCredentials()`; added auth endpoints (`/api/auth/register`, `/api/auth/login`, `/api/auth/logout`, `/api/auth/me`), CSRF token endpoint (`/api/csrf-token`), user-scoped booking history (`/api/my-bookings`); protected booking creation with auth + CSRF; seeded demo user (`demo@example.com` / `demo1234`)\n- **BookingStore.cs** \u2014 Added `GetBookingsForUser(userId)` for user-scoped booking queries\n\n### Backend Tests\n- **RestaurantBooking.Tests.csproj** \u2014 Added `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Testing`\n- **ApiTests.cs** (new) \u2014 13 HTTP integration tests covering: restaurant list, availability (success, unknown restaurant, invalid party), register+login+logout flow, booking creation with/without auth, CSRF validation, user booking isolation (scoped-to-user), overlapping reservation conflict (409), demo user login, invalid credentials\n\n### Frontend\n- **openapi/restaurant-booking.json** \u2014 Updated with auth endpoints, CSRF token, booking history, security schemes\n- **orval.config.ts** \u2014 Switched from `client: \"fetch\"` to `client: \"react-query\"` with custom fetch mutator for CSRF/credentials, generating TanStack Query hooks\n- **src/lib/api-mutator.ts** (new) \u2014 Custom fetch wrapper that adds `X-XSRF-TOKEN` header on mutations, sends `credentials: \"include\"` for cookie auth, exposes `fetchCsrfToken()`/`getCsrfTokenValue()` for SPA auth flow\n- **src/App.tsx** \u2014 Rewritten to use generated `useListRestaurants`, `useListAvailableSlots`, `useCreateBooking`, `useGetCurrentUser`, `useGetMyBookings` TanStack Query hooks; added auth UI (login/register form, auth bar with logout, demo credentials hint); added \"My bookings\" section; shows sign-in prompt when unauthenticated before booking\n- **src/generated/booking-client.ts** \u2014 Regenerated by Orval with TanStack Query hooks (unchanged from generation output)\n\n### Documentation\n- **README.md** \u2014 Updated with auth setup, seeded demo user, auth/protected endpoint tables, CSRF flow description, HTTP integration test notes\n\n### Delegation Failure Note\nBoth `delegate_workflow` calls (swarm-research and swarm-review) failed due to the delegation tool rejecting the stage/agent configurations despite matching the documented budget limits. Implementation proceeded directly with thorough codebase analysis.\n\n### Checks Results\nAll 9 deterministic checks pass:\n- `dotnet build`: 0 warnings, 0 errors\n- `dotnet test`: 21/21 passed (8 domain + 13 HTTP integration)\n- `dotnet format verify-no-changes`: clean\n- `npm install`, `build`, `typecheck`, `lint`, `format:check`, `deadcode`: all pass\n\n### Known Limitations\n- Demo user is seeded via `EnsureCreated()` in the startup path \u2014 subsequent runs won't re-seed (uses `Users.Any()` guard)\n- CSRF token is bound to user identity; after login/logout/register, the SPA must re-fetch the CSRF token (the test helpers and frontend code handle this)\n- Register endpoint doesn't require CSRF (acceptable: no existing session to protect)\n- Overlap test uses party size 6 to force single-table conflict (ember-6 is the only table with capacity \u2265 6 at Ember Table)",
